Description:
Two Storey Home on Three Acres.
"Ashwood" Well positioned on Catona Crescent, this solid, two storey family home offers rural living close to town. The appealing residence has exposed brick walls and plenty of natural timber features throughout. Downstairs features a blackwood timber kitchen with gas and electric cooking, formal lounge, dining/family room plus a huge rumpus room. Upstairs includes four generous bedrooms, main with walk in robe and ensuite with spa. Evaporative cooling and floor heating. Double garage under roofline with direct house access. Set on approximately three acres, the property includes a 6 metre by 6 metre (approx.) brick garage/workshop, a 6 metre by 12 metre (approx.) Colourbond shed with concrete floor and power, established plants and trees, vegetable gardens, fruit trees, domestic bore and automatic sprinkler system. Town water and natural gas are connected.
The best of both worlds are on offer here - a rural living feel, and town conveniences. Inspection available by appointment.

Description:
Executive Living - A Class Above
Immaculately presented, four year old home in a secure, back-of-block location.
With no expense having been spared by the current owner, the stunning home features a spacious open plan living area with ceramic tiles, kitchen with Caesar stone bench tops/splash back and a walk in pantry, and dining area with sliding doors to the lovely undercover alfresco area with ceiling fan and neat, low maintenance yard. Three generous bedrooms with built-in robes and TV points, and the main with walk-in robe and ensuite with floor-to-ceiling tiles and a walk in shower.

It's all here in this excellent location within short walking distance to the river. This home is certainly one to be impressed by. Indulge yourself, you certainly deserve this class of living.

Description:
Entertainment delight
If you love to entertain, this contemporary home is for you! The home comprises three bedrooms and two living areas. The master bedroom is located to the front of the home and has ensuite with oversized vanity with double bowls and walk in robe. Stunning galley style kitchen offers a pop of red in the splashback, gas cooktop, underbench oven and and a large island bench overlooking the family/meals area. From here you are lead out to a sensational outdoor entertaining area that wraps around two sides of the home giving you a dining, lounge and play area all in one. It then offers seamless views of the heated inground swimming pool. Imagine spending the endless summer nights out here! There is a double garage with a real roller door and 16 solar panels to the roof. The attention to detail in this home is second to none, and you will not be disappointed. Make an inspection today.

Description:
Motivated vendor says sell!!
Perfectly located literally a stone's throw from the Mighty Murray River is this brick veneer home offering 3 bedrooms plus study and two living areas. The sunken lounge has an abundance of glazing and is a generous size. To the rear of the home is the open plan kitchen/family/meals which overlooks both an alfresco courtyard and fernery area. The kitchen has electric hot plates and oven and has plenty of storage. The master bedroom comprises robe and ensuite. The family bathroom with corner spa and separate shower service the remaining bedrooms. The double garage has direct access into the study which is adjacent to the kitchen making it ideal as a home office. Climate throughout the home is controlled by the ducted reverse cycle heating/cooling unit. Outside is a sensationally private courtyard for all your outdoor entertaining needs which then opens up to a good size rear yard.

Description:
Choice River End Location
This solid three bedroom family home is sited on a generous 843 square metre block in a great location, only a very short walk to the banks of the Murray River and the surrounding bush land/walking tracks.

Don't miss your opportunity to secure this fantastic home or investment. Call our office today.
